          The best time to visit Amsterdam is during the spring (April to June)
          when the weather is mild and the city's famous tulip fields are in
          full bloom. This season also features vibrant festivals and fewer
          tourists compared to summer. Fall (September to November) is another
          great option, as the crowds thin out and the foliage turns beautiful
          shades of orange and red. Each season has its charm, but spring and
          fall offer a lovely balance of pleasant weather and cultural
          experiences. Summer is popular but can be crowded, while winter,
          especially around the holidays, brings a magical atmosphere with
          festive lights and markets.
        </p>
